# Mapillary Coverage

A CLI-only pipeline that computes Mapillary coverage for OSM highways in Germany.

## Setup

Prerequisites:

- `uv` and Python 3.12 for local runs
- Docker with `docker compose` for container runs
- a Mapillary token via `config/local.toml` or `MAPILLARY_ACCESS_TOKEN`

Local bootstrap:

```bash
uv sync
source .venv/bin/activate
cp config/local.toml.example config/local.toml
```

Important paths:

- `config/default.toml`: tracked defaults
- `config/local.toml`: local overrides and secrets
- `resources/bundeslaender.geojson`: reference geometry
- `data/cache/tile_cache`: checked-in tile cache
- `data/osm/raw`, `data/osm/processed`, `data/mapillary/coverage`: internal pipeline data
- `output`: final CSV and metadata

## CLI

```bash
uv run mapillary-coverage show-config
uv run mapillary-coverage run-pipeline --dry-run
uv run mapillary-coverage run-pipeline
```

The production shell entrypoint is [scripts/run_mapillary_pipeline.sh](/home/simon/mapillary_coverage/scripts/run_mapillary_pipeline.sh).

## Docker

Without VPN:

```bash
docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml up --build mapillary_worker
```

With VPN via Gluetun:

```bash
export NORD_USER="..."
export NORD_PASS="..."

docker compose \
  -f docker/docker-compose.yml \
  -f docker/docker-compose.vpn.yml \
  up --build mapillary_worker
```

Stop and clean up:

```bash
docker compose \
  -f docker/docker-compose.yml \
  -f docker/docker-compose.vpn.yml \
  down --remove-orphans
```

## Server Run

Minimum flow:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/vizsim/mapillary_coverage.git
cd mapillary_coverage
cp config/local.toml.example config/local.toml

docker compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml up --build mapillary_worker
```

For a one-command update, run, and push workflow, use [scripts/run_and_push.sh](/home/simon/mapillary_coverage/scripts/run_and_push.sh).

## Result

The [`/output` folder](https://github.com/vizsim/mapillary_coverage/tree/main/output) holds the latest CSV and metadata files.

